persistHouseholds

int persistHouseholds(java.lang.Integer zoneId,
                      GeographyType geoType,
                      java.util.Set<Household> hhs,
                      Version version,
                      boolean writeAllocated)
Writes discretized or allocated households by zone to the database

Parameters:
zoneId - zone ID
geoType - geography type
hhs - a set of household objects
version - the Version object for this PopSyn II run
writeAllocated - a boolean where true indicates the insertion of allocated households and false indicates the insertion of discretized households.
Returns:
0 for successful execution and -1 for fatal error.
